					TestoTeoria: "<p>The pathway of the Lung Tendon-Muscle channel starts from the thumb, meets the thenar eminence, passes over the radial wrist, proceeds along the inner side of the forearm, reaches the elbow, and then continues along the anterolateral surface of the arm. Afterward, it converges in the chest, under the armpit, and reaches the supraclavicular fossa ([.12.ST.*.]). In the chest, it branches towards the cardiac region and reaches the lower ribs.</p>",
